Package: PhotomossR
Type: Package
Title: Calculates Spectral Indices for Multiple Areas per Photo
Version: 1.1
Date: 2023-01-16
Author: Manuel Molina-Bustamante with essential collaboration from Indradatta deCastro-Arrazola
Maintainer: Manuel Molina-Bustamante <manuel.molinab@uam.es>
Authors@R: c(person("Manuel", "Molina-Bustamante", email = "manuel.molinab@uam.es", role = c("aut", "cre")), 
person("Indradatta", "deCastro-Arrazola", email = "indra@mncn.csic.es", role = c("aut")),
person("Kyle", "Doherty", email = "kdoherty@mpgranch.com", role = c("aut", "com")),
person("Nagore G.", "Medina", email = "nagore.garcia@uam.es", role = c("aut", "ths")))
Description: Calculates spectral vegetation and color indices (NDVI...) in multiple
    VIS (=VISible) and NIR (=Near InfraRed) pairs of photos. The package is 
    heavily based on package crustcover (available at GitHub username mosscoder).
License: GPL (>= 2)
Depends: raster
Imports: dplyr, rgeos, data.table, tiff, jpeg, sp, RColorBrewer, spatstat, RImageJROI
BugReports: https://github.com/MMolBus/PhotomossR/issues
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
